'''Taga-no-Miya''' ({{ill|多賀宮|ja|多賀宮}}) is an auxiliary shrine ({{ill|betsugu|ja|別宮}}) located within the precincts of {{ill|Toyouke Daijingu|ja|豊受大神宮}}, also known as the Outer Shrine ({{ill|Geku|ja|外宮}}), in {{ill|Ise City|ja|伊勢市}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県}}.

== Overview ==
Taga-no-Miya is situated on {{ill|Hinokioyama|ja|檜尾山}}, south of the main sanctuary of the Outer Shrine. The term "betsugu" means "separate shrine," indicating its reverence second only to the main sanctuary. Among the four auxiliary shrines of the Outer Shrine—{{ill|Tsuchi-no-Miya|ja|土宮}}, {{ill|Kaze-no-Miya|ja|風宮}}, and {{ill|Tsukiyomi-no-Miya (Geku)|ja|月夜見宮}} located outside the precincts—Taga-no-Miya is the oldest.

The deity enshrined here is the {{ill|Aramitama|ja|荒魂}} (wild spirit) of {{ill|Toyouke Omikami|ja|豊受大御神}}. This association grants Taga-no-Miya the highest status among the auxiliary shrines.

== Deity ==
* '''Toyouke Omikami Aramitama''' ({{ill|豊受大御神荒魂|ja|豊受大御神荒魂}})

In ancient texts like the "{{ill|Yamatohime-no-Mikoto Seiki|ja|倭姫命世記}}" and "{{ill|Ise Nisho Daijinguu Go Chinza Shidai-ki|ja|伊勢二所皇太神宮御鎮座次第記}}", Toyouke Omikami Aramitama is referred to by other names, such as {{ill|Ibukidono Nushi|ja|伊吹戸主}}, a deity born from the purification ritual of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ}} after returning from the underworld.

== History ==
The shrine is believed to have been established around 478 CE during the founding of the Outer Shrine. Although previously referred to as "Takamiya," the name "Taga-no-Miya" became official after the Meiji period. Despite sharing the name "Taga," it has no relation to {{ill|Taga Taisha|ja|多賀大社}}.

== Festivals and Rituals ==
Taga-no-Miya observes rituals similar to those of the Outer Shrine, including:
* {{ill|Kinensai|ja|祈年祭}}
* {{ill|Tsukinamisai|ja|月次祭}}
* {{ill|Kannamesai|ja|神嘗祭}}
* {{ill|Niinamesai|ja|新嘗祭}}

Imperial offerings ({{ill|heihaku|ja|幣帛}}) are presented during these ceremonies.

== Architecture ==
The shrine's structure follows the {{ill|Shimmei-zukuri|ja|神明造}} architectural style, featuring thatched roofs with chigi and katsuogi. The shrine faces south, and adjacent plots are reserved for relocation during the {{ill|Shikinen Sengu|ja|式年遷宮}} ritual.

== Access ==
* 12-minute walk from {{ill|Ise Station|ja|伊勢市駅}} (JR Sangu Line / Kintetsu Line)
* 5-minute walk from {{ill|Mie Kotsu|ja|三重交通}} bus stop "Geku-mae"
* 2 km from {{ill|Ise Nishi Interchange|ja|伊勢西インターチェンジ}} on the Ise Expressway
* Free parking available

